1. Boot Sox: These are an essential accessory to go with a gents jacket, and can help protect the shoes and keep them warm in cold temperatures.

2. Belt: Adding a coordinating leather or canvas belt to a gents jacket can help enhance the look and complete the outfit.

3. Scarf: A scarf can further keep the chill out, and can also add a stylish accent to the ensemble.

4. Cashmere Gloves: A pair of cashmere gloves will ensure the hands stay warm and cosy.

5. Overcoat: For those extra cold days, a jacket can be enhanced with an overcoat in a complimentary color.

6. Tie & Bow tie: A tie or bow tie can add extra style and flair to a gents look.

7. Hat: A hat can finish off the look and keep the head warm during cold weather.

8. Suspenders: Adding suspenders can help the gents look more dapper and formal.

9. Wallet: A coordinating wallet can not only help keep the money safe, but also add a finishing touch to the outfit.

10. Pocket square: This simple accessory can add a touch of color and spice to the outfit.

11. Lapel pin: Add a lapel pin or two to stand up to the jacket with a little something extra.

12. Socks: Dress socks that match the look is a must to help complement the hair of the boots.

13. Shoe polish: Using a shoe polish can help to ensure the boots look their finest for the jacket.

14. Glasses: Add a pair of glasses to your look to keep the cold out and look good at the same time.

15. Umbrella: For those rainy days, an umbrella can help keep the rain away and make the look complete.

16. Perfume: Adding a light spritz of a coordinating fragrance can add another layer of sophistication to the look.

17. Walking cane: For a truly dapper look, a walking cane can really set off the gents jacket perfectly.

18. Cufflinks: Cufflinks can be the perfect accessory to add some sparkle and flair to the jacket.

19. Pocket watch: For a classic and timeless look, adding a pocket watch completes the gents jacket.

20. Handkerchief: For a polished and completed look, a handkerchief can match the pocket square or pocket watch.

For the IDIYA Colombo Bunk bed, some popular and relevant product recommendations could include:

1. Bed Linens – sheets, blankets, and pillowcases specially designed to fit bunk beds.

4. Drawer Set – A number of drawers built into the frame of the bunk bed for extra storage and organization. 

5. Staircase – Designed for easy of accessibility for the top bunk when the bed is elevated.

6. Lamps – To provide easy light during nighttime hours without blinding those who are sleeping. 

7. Curtain – A bunk bed can provide extra privacy and cozy feel with the use of a curtain.

8. Desk and Chair – Often can fit underneath the bottom bunk for reusable, versatile space. 

9. Hooks – To hang items like bags or clothing for easy access.

10. Bookshelf – For under-bed storage of books, school supplies, and more. 

11. TV Stand – For housing a television set in the bedroom.

12. Storage Baskets – To neatly hold items stored in the bunk bed. 

13. Clothes Hangers – To provide additional storage and organization options.

14. Fan – Ideal for cooling during the hot New Zealand summer. 

15. Inflatable Foot Pad –To protect feet from the hard frame underneath the bed.

16. Stickers – To add fun, creative flair to the bed.

17. Rug – To provide a cozy, warm element to the room.

18. Wall Art – To make the bunk bed area a bit more personalized for the user. 

19. Decorative Throw Pillows – To provide a bit of style to the bunk bed. 

20. Cushions or Footstool – They can provide extra comfort for those using the bed.

column2:
RESEARCH
1. Target market. Identify the target demographic in NZ that might be interested in purchasing the product - parents with young children/infants, people transitioning from one home to another, college students/young adults, people looking for a minimalistic, modern design in their bedrooms. 

2. Popular products. Research current product trends in NZ to determine which products are the most popular and relevant to the target market - organic bedding, waterproof mattress protectors, adjustable bed frames, designer headboards, firm pillows, light blocking curtains, adjustable bedside tables, compact storage solutions, modern wall art, minimalistic floor lamps, etc.

3. Quality products. Identify products with the highest customer satisfaction ratings and most relevant features to go along with the bed base - memory foam mattress, duvet sets, bedding sets (sheets, blanket, throw/quilt), mattress toppers, Moses baskets, night lamps, blackout curtains, bear-proof mattress protectors, 3-piece art set, etc.

RECOMMENDATIONS
1. Organic bedding - cotton sheets, bamboo duvet covers, wool blanket and throw.
2. Waterproof mattress protectors - cotton terry and synthetic wool.
3. Adjustable bed frames - modular and adjustable beds.
4. Designer headboards - wooden, fabric and metal headboards.
5. Firm pillows - memory foam, bamboo memory foam and micro-fiber pillows.
6. Light blocking curtains - light blocking curtains with blackout lining.
7. Adjustable bedside tables - adjustable bedside tables with wheels, and drawers.
8. Compact storage solutions - under-bed storage boxes, storage cabinets, and storage cubes. 
9. Modern wall art - prints and paintings with modern, minimalistic design.
10. Minimalistic floor lamps - LED lamps with adjustable light settings.
11. Memory foam mattress - foam mattress with adjustable firmness levels.
12. Duvet sets - micro-fiber or bamboo duvets and matching shams.
13. Bedding sets - sheets, blankets, and throws in cotton, bamboo or wool.
14. Mattress toppers - memory foam, bamboo memory foam, and synthetic wool mattress toppers.
15. Moses baskets - bassinet in natural, breathable materials.
16. Night lamps - LED lamps with adjustable settings.
17. Blackout curtains - dark colored curtains with thick, blackout lining.
18. Bear-proof mattress protectors - thick, quilted mattress protectors made from cotton or synthetic wool.
19. 3-Piece art set - paintings, sketches and prints with modern, minimalistic design.
20. Wall shelves - modular shelves, stackable shelves and adjustable shelves for organizing bedroom and storage needs.

17) Hanging garment bags - Perfect for keeping wedding gowns and other special occasion wear. 

18) Summer and winter wardrobe organisers - Makes it easy for a wardrobe to be quickly adapted for the change of seasons. 

19) Drawer organisers - Keeps items organised and within reach. 

20) Hooks and coat hangers - Perfect for quickly adding an extra item of clothing to the wardrobe.
